
[1]petulant

   PET'ULANT, a. [L. petulans.] Saucy; pert or forward with fretfulness or
   sourness of temper; as a petulant youth.

   1. Manifesting petulance; proceeding from pettishness; as a petulant
   demand; a petulant answer.

   2. Wanton; freakish in passion.
